  "programNotes": "<ul> <li>Students with Chemistry 11 and Pre-Calculus 12 or equivalents must take CHEM <a href=\"#/courses/Hk0p0w6XV\">091</a> before enrolling in CHEM 1<a href=\"#/courses/r11A0D6XN\">02</a>. Students with Chemistry 12 and Pre-Calculus 12 or equivalents should not take CHEM <a href=\"#/courses/Hk0p0w6XV\">091</a>.</li> <li>EOS <a href=\"#/courses/HyGhmO67E\">120</a> is a prerequisite to EOS <a href=\"#/courses/B1dh7_T7V\">313</a>.</li> <li> <div>EOS 325 requires a computing prerequisite, which EOS <a href=\"#/courses/S1tn7d6QE\">314</a> satisfies. EOS <a href=\"#/courses/S1tn7d6QE\">314</a> should therefore be taken in the third year, and EOS <a href=\"#/courses/Hk9nQOp7V\">325</a> in fourth year, unless EOS <a href=\"#/courses/Hk9nQOp7V\">325</a> prerequisites are met through other computing experience.</div> </li> <li>Most 400-level EOS classes are offered in alternate years. A schedule of when each class is offered is available on the School of Earth and Ocean Sciences website.</li> </ul>",
